<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-54-0507 </DOCNO><TEXT>Superconducting solenoid systems which produce large magnetic fields canbe designed to utilize flux conservation to cancel fluctuations in theambient magnetic field in which they are located. Such self-shieldingsolenoids could be very useful for mass spectroscopy of trapped particles,nuclear magnetic resonance experiments, and magnetic resonance imaging.</TEXT></DOC>